Additionally, Brunson's strong play has sparked aspirations of representing the United States at the 2024 Olympics in Paris.

name: Memorial Hermann liver transplants
summary: Several news articles report that a Houston hospital has suspended its liver and kidney transplant programs after discovering irregularities in patient records. The New York Times alleges that a prominent surgeon, Dr. Steve Bynon, secretly denied liver transplants to eligible patients. According to NBC News, Dr. Bynon manipulated the electronic records system, making it appear that patients were not eligible for transplants. The Houston Chronicle reports that the hospital has stopped accepting new transplant patients and is reviewing all past transplant cases. USA Today identifies Dr. Bynon as the surgeon accused of denying livers to patients. The hospital's transplant coordinator, Alex S. Chang, notified the United Network for Organ Sharing about the irregularities, leading to the suspension of the programs.

name: Prostate cancer
summary: Multiple news outlets have reported on the death of former football player O.J. Simpson, who passed away at age 76 after a battle with prostate cancer. The news has prompted discussions about prostate cancer awareness and screening. Former National Institutes of Health (NIH) director Francis Collins shared his own experience with prostate cancer and emphasized the importance of medical research. Experts have highlighted the need for increased awareness about the disease, as many men are reluctant to discuss or seek treatment for prostate cancer. Advances in screening technology are providing more accurate and affordable options. However, a recent study has raised concerns about the limitations of prostate-specific antigen (PSA) tests in detecting aggressive forms of the cancer. Despite the challenges, organizations like Penn Medicine are actively educating men about prostate cancer screening and treatment options.
